  "text": "By negating one symmetric variable of the function , the E-symmetry is converted to NE-symmetry. Therefore, in the classification process, only NE-symmetry and multiform symmetry are considered. The multiform symmetry cannot be simply regarded as NE-symmetry, and must be manipulated separately. Many existing classification methods [CITATION_1] [15] neglected this difference.",
